*.cs text
*.shader text diff=csharp

# Unity assets are byte-exact, NEVER line-ending converted.
#
# These previously carried `eol=lf`, which tells git the file is text and to rewrite its line
# endings on every checkout. Unity had written the scene in BINARY serialization despite the project
# being set to Force Text, so git was mangling binary bytes in transit: the machine that generated
# the file was fine, but anyone who cloned or pulled got a corrupted scene that opened empty. They
# would then rebuild it locally, which regenerates every in-scene NetworkObject hash and breaks co-op
# with "NetworkPrefab hash was not found".
#
# `-text` disables all conversion regardless of whether the file is YAML or binary. These scenes are
# generated by the build script rather than hand-edited, so losing textual diffs costs nothing next
# to guaranteeing every machine gets identical bytes.
*.unity   -text merge=unityyamlmerge
*.asset   -text merge=unityyamlmerge
*.prefab  -text merge=unityyamlmerge
*.mat     -text merge=unityyamlmerge
*.meta    -text merge=unityyamlmerge
*.controller -text merge=unityyamlmerge
*.inputactions -text merge=unityyamlmerge

